PasswordAspect
==============

PasswordAspect provides several helpers and methods to deal with usermodels
that have passwords.

All you need to do is to provide two string columns 'hashed_password'
and 'salt' in your models table and include PasswordAspect in the model.

For more information take a look into the Rdoc

